.TH vzyum 8 "May 23, 2005" "Open Virtuozzo" "Virtual Private Servers"
.SH NAME
vzyum \- yum wrapper for use with Open Virtuozzo's VPS
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBvzyum\fR \fIVPSID\fR \fIyumoption\fR [...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This is a simple \fByum\fR(\fI8\fR) wrapper, which makes it easy to use
\fByum\fR(\fI8\fR) from the Open Virtuozzo host system command line. Use it
like ordinary \fByum\fR(\fI8\fR), just give VPS ID as a first argument.
.PP
The main point of using \fBvzyum\fR instead of yum is in this case yum cache
is shared between VPSes, so you don't have to download a package update
100 times if you have 100 VPSes based on the same OS template.
.SH EXAMPLES
\fB\f(CWvzyum 123 update\fR
.PP
\fB\f(CWvzyum 123 install mysql\fR
.PP
\fB\f(CWvzyum 123 -d10 check-update\fR
.SH SEE ALSO
.BI vzpkgcache (8)\fR,
.BI vzctl (8)\fR,
.BI yum (8)\fR.
